## Analytics — warn up-front when the graph exceeds the triple limit

Context: On a large store, Run Analysis failed only after the background task
loaded everything: "Triple count (7641879) exceeds max_triples (500000)". The
500k limit was a hardcoded default (`MetricsRequest.max_triples`, read by the
compute endpoints as `data.get("max_triples", 500_000)`, enforced in
`GraphBuilder._load_triples`). Two problems: (1) the triple count is already
known via `/dtwin/sync/stats`, so the user should be warned *before* running;
(2) the error advised "use a predicate or class filter", but the guard runs on
the FULL load — filters are applied later in `_build_graph` and do not reduce
what is read, so they never lift the limit.

Fix:
- Made the limit a configurable setting `analytics_max_triples`
  (env `ONTOBRICKS_ANALYTICS_MAX_TRIPLES`, default 500_000); both compute
  endpoints now default to it.
- `/dtwin/sync/stats` returns `analytics_max_triples`; the Analytics page reads
  it alongside `total_triples` and, when over the limit, shows a red banner and
  disables Run Analysis up-front (with a backstop check on click).
- The async compute endpoint fails fast (clear `ValidationError`) when the known
  triple count already exceeds the limit, instead of spawning a doomed task.
- Corrected the `GraphBuilder._load_triples` message (and added a code comment)
  to advise reducing the synced graph or raising the limit — not filtering.

Changes:

1. src/shared/config/settings.py
   New `analytics_max_triples` setting (env `ONTOBRICKS_ANALYTICS_MAX_TRIPLES`).
2. src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py
   Both `max_triples` defaults now use `settings.analytics_max_triples`;
   `/metrics/compute` pre-checks `get_aggregate_stats().total` and raises a
   clear `ValidationError` when over the limit; `/sync/stats` returns
   `analytics_max_triples`.
3. src/back/core/graph_analysis/GraphBuilder.py
   Accurate over-limit message + clarifying comment (filters don't reduce the
   load).
4. src/front/templates/partials/dtwin/_query_analytics.html
   `_loadEntityTypes()` captures `total_triples` / `analytics_max_triples`,
   shows `_showOverLimitBanner()` and disables Run Analysis when over the limit;
   `analyticsCompute()` backstop blocks a doomed run.
5. docs/user-guide.md
   Documented the graph-size limit and the up-front warning.

