## Analytics — always render the last run in the result tabs on open

Context: Opening the Analytics section should immediately populate the result
tabs (PageRank, Betweenness, Degree, Closeness, Clustering, Data Model Health)
with the last stored analysis. `analyticsResume()` checked for an in-flight
`graph_analytics` task *first* and only rendered the stored result in the `else`
branch — so a running (or stale/leftover) background task delayed or blocked the
last run from showing in the tabs.

Fix: `analyticsResume()` now calls `analyticsLoadLatest()` unconditionally first
(so the tabs are populated right away from the `graph_analytics` cache),
then checks for a running task and, if present, re-shows the spinner and resumes
waiting — the last result stays visible underneath until the new one lands.
`analyticsLoadLatest()` shows the spinner (with a "Loading the last analysis…"
message) while it fetches/renders the stored result.

Changes:

1. src/front/templates/partials/dtwin/_query_analytics.html
   - `analyticsResume()` reordered: render last stored run first, resume any
     in-flight task afterwards.
   - `analyticsLoadLatest()` toggles `#analyticsSpinner` (temporary "Loading the
     last analysis…" message) around the fetch/render.

