## Analytics — add a "History" tab listing every analysis run

Context: With analytics now persisting only the LAST result per
`(domain, version)`, there was no way to see how many analyses had been run, when,
with what scope, or whether any failed. Requested a new tab (after AI Insights)
that lists all analyses ran (history).

Design: added an append-only `graph_analytics_runs` trace (one immutable,
lightweight row per launch — success or failure) alongside the existing
`graph_analytics` cache. The cache still backs the result tabs and the cockpit;
the new trace backs the History tab only. Capped server-side at 100 rows per
`(domain, version)` (oldest pruned on insert) to stay bounded. Mirrors the
`build_runs` store conventions (lazy `_ensure_*` self-heal DDL, best-effort
writes, `_KNOWN_TABLES`).

