## Analytics — resume the running spinner when returning to the page

Context: With the analysis now running in a background TaskManager task, leaving
the Analytics page (to Ontology or another section/page) and coming back while a
computation was still running showed no progress indicator — the spinner state
lived only in the `analyticsCompute()` call that started it. Users had no signal
the analysis was still in flight.

Fix: on section open, query the global task list for an in-flight
`graph_analytics` task; if one exists, re-show the spinner, disable the button,
and resume waiting (`waitForTask`) before loading the stored result. Otherwise
just render the last stored result as before.

