## Document `uv.lock` deploy guardrails in rules + deploy skill

Context: The Databricks Apps deploy runs `uv run --frozen` and installs verbatim
from `uv.lock`. Two recurring failure modes have broken deploys before: (1) the
lock's wheel URLs getting rewritten from the public CDN
(`files.pythonhosted.org`) to the internal proxy
(`pypi-proxy.dev.databricks.com`, which cold-caches fresh wheels and times out),
and (2) the lock drifting out of sync with `pyproject.toml`. The dev shell
defaults `UV_INDEX_URL`/`PIP_INDEX_URL` to the proxy, so any bare `uv lock` /
`uv sync` silently churns the lock to proxy URLs. Verified the current lock is
clean (3653 URLs, all `files.pythonhosted.org`, zero proxy; `uv lock --check`
against the public index → exit 0) and captured the checks/rules so the issue
can't recur.

Changes:

1. .cursor/09-package-management.mdc
   New "`uv.lock` is deployment-critical — DO NOT let it churn" section: the two
   failure modes, the day-to-day `--frozen` rule, the public-index re-lock
   command, the read-only pre-deploy verification commands (URL host check +
   `UV_INDEX_URL=https://pypi.org/simple uv lock --check`), and the
   `git checkout -- uv.lock` recovery for accidental churn.
2. .claude/skills/deploy/SKILL.md
   Added pre-flight step 5 (verify lock is on the public CDN and in sync via the
   public index) and two new "Don't" entries (no bare `uv lock`/`uv sync`; never
   commit proxy URLs).
3. .cursor/08-testing-and-deployment.mdc
   Cross-referenced the new lockfile section from the Deployment bullet.

