## Preflight soft-dependency check (psql) in deploy.sh

Context: `psql` (libpq) is only validated deep inside
`bootstrap-lakebase-perms.sh` (step 11), so on a Lakebase-target deploy a
missing client was discovered only AFTER the whole bundle had already been
deployed and started. Surface optional tooling up front during preflight,
warn with an actionable list, and prompt to continue.

Changes:

1. scripts/deploy.sh
   - Step 1a: split tooling check into hard deps (databricks, python3 — still
     abort) and a new soft-dep pass. `check_soft_cmd` collects every missing
     optional tool into `_missing_soft`; `psql` is checked only when the run
     will actually reach the Lakebase GRANT bootstrap (`$IS_LAKEBASE &&
     $DO_BOOTSTRAP`).
   - On any missing soft dep: warn, list each tool + install hint, then prompt
     `Continue anyway? [y/N]` on a TTY (abort via `die` on no), or warn-and-
     continue on a non-interactive shell so CI is never blocked.
   - Updated the Prerequisites header comment to list python3 + psql.

