## Domain edit-lock (single-editor, heartbeat TTL, admin take-over)

Context: Concurrency control for DRAFT domain versions. Previously two users
could open and edit the same (domain, version) at once, racing last-write-wins
saves. This adds a single-editor lock: the first opener of a DRAFT version
edits it; later openers land read-only with a banner naming the current
editor. The lock lives in Lakebase (multi-replica safe) with a heartbeat +
TTL auto-expiry (closed tab / crash self-heals in ~90s), and an app-admin can
force "take over" a held lock. Server enforcement is authoritative
(PermissionMiddleware); the UI re-uses the existing read-only CSS gating.

Changes:

1. src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/schema.sql
   - New table domain_edit_locks (domain_id, version, holder_email,
     holder_name, holder_session, acquired_at, heartbeat_at; PK
     (domain_id, version)) keyed by domain row with ON DELETE CASCADE.
2. src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/store.py
   - Added _EDIT_LOCK_TTL_S = 90 and "domain_edit_locks" to _KNOWN_TABLES.
   - _ensure_domain_edit_locks_table() lazy self-heal (same ownership-safe
     pattern as _ensure_collab_tables; guarded by _edit_locks_ready).
   - Store methods with TTL semantics: acquire_edit_lock (atomic upsert —
     wins when free / stale / self / force), heartbeat_edit_lock (refresh iff
     still holder; held=False on take-over), release_edit_lock (holder-only),
     force_release_edit_lock (admin, unconditional), get_edit_lock (+ computed
     stale), and the _get_edit_lock_row / _edit_lock_row_to_dict helpers.
3. src/back/objects/registry/EditLockService.py (new)
   - Stateless orchestrator over the store methods. Resolves the Lakebase
     store via RegistryFactory.lakebase (same path as
     SettingsService.check_lakebase_permissions); identity from the request
     (user_email / x-forwarded-preferred-username / session_id). Methods:
     status (non-forcing acquire → edit/view/none), heartbeat, acquire
     (admin-only force), release, on_domain_loaded (release prev + acquire
     new), release_for_session, force_release, and blocking_holder (the
     middleware gate helper). Degrades to mode "none" when Lakebase/psycopg
     is unavailable.
4. src/api/routers/internal/domain.py
   - load-from-uc now attaches a {lock} block on success (releases the prior
     version's lock, acquires the new DRAFT one). New routes GET
     /domain/edit-lock, POST /domain/edit-lock/{heartbeat,acquire,release}.
     set-version-status force-releases the lock when a version leaves DRAFT.
     save-to-uc forwards actor_email for the defence-in-depth lock re-check.
5. src/api/routers/internal/home.py
   - reset-session releases the session's edit lock before wiping the session.
6. src/shared/fastapi/main.py
   - PermissionMiddleware: edit-lock gate after the lifecycle gate — a
     non-holder mutating a status-gated edit route on a DRAFT version gets a
     403 ("being edited by <holder>"). Admins are NOT exempt (must take over
     first). New _session_edit_lock_holder helper (only runs on already-gated
     mutating routes — no per-request Lakebase cost on reads).
7. src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py
   - save_domain_to_uc gains actor_email + a defence-in-depth lock-ownership
     re-check (ConflictError when another user holds the lock).
8. src/front/static/global/js/edit-lock.js (new)
   - On load GETs the lock: editor → 30s heartbeat (flips to read-only +
     toast on take-over); viewer → body.read-only-locked + dismissible banner
     ("being edited by <holder>") with an admin "Take over editing" button.
     Releases on pagehide/beforeunload via fetch keepalive (CSRF-safe; the
     server TTL is the real safety net).
9. src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css
   - Folded .read-only-locked into the shared read-only selector group
     (replace_all of body:is(.read-only-version, .role-viewer) →
     …, .read-only-locked), so every existing write-surface gate applies to
     locked viewers with no per-control edits. Added #editLockBanner styling.
10. src/front/static/global/js/permissions.js
    - canEditOntology() now also returns false when window.editLockMode ==
      'view' (set by edit-lock.js).
11. src/front/templates/base.html
    - Loads edit-lock.js (deferred, after version-check.js).
12. Tests: tests/units/registry/test_edit_lock_store.py (mocked-cursor store
    methods: free/self/stale/force/heartbeat-lost), test_edit_lock_service.py
    (mode shaping, force gating, blocking_holder), tests/units/api/
    test_edit_lock_endpoints.py (request wiring; sync _run() helper avoids the
    pre-existing async-endpoint event-loop clash), and an edit-lock gate class
    in tests/units/auth/test_permission_middleware.py (non-holder 403, holder
    passes, admin not exempt, no check on reads).
13. docs/deployment.md (domain_edit_locks in the Lakebase schema map),
    docs/sphinx/api/app.objects.registry.rst (EditLockService automodule).

